git config --list

1. Enable Colored Output Globally
To enable color in Git's output across all repositories:

git config --global color.ui auto

2. Customize Specific Color Settings

Git allows you to customize colors for various elements. For example, to change the color of the status output:

git config --global color.status.changed "yellow"
git config --global color.status.untracked "red"

3. View Your Current Color Settings

To see your current color configurations:
git config --list | grep color
4. Reset to Default Colors

If you want to revert to Git's default color settings:
git config --global --unset color.ui
